description:
"Someone here is not me" (1978), by Cecília Navas (1954 - 1999), artwork label. 
This piece belongs to The Museum of the Incomplete Absolute. 

---------

The Museum of the Incomplete Absolute (MotIA) is the largest museum on Earth. Our collection comprises all works of art created since the beginning of human history. Unfortunately, we don't have the image rights to any of them, so we can only legally share their labels with the public.

Bruno Lorenz (https://twitter.com/brunolorenz) is the CCO (Chief Curator Officer) of the MotIA.
